						<summary>

						<p>On a rock face on the west of the Veṅkaṭēśvara temple on a hill.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1197, <hi rend="italic">Bhāva, Jyēshṭha,</hi> ba. 5, Saturday (?), corresponding to A.D. 1274 May 26. (Bhāva corresponds to Śaka 1196).</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift of 1 <hi rend="italic">Khaṇḍuga</hi> of land to god Bhairava of Vaikuṇṭhapuram. Mentions Ānandanātha, probably as the donor of the grant.</p>						

						</summary>
